"OH MY GOD i think i talk about hattie b's every day. this place is by far the best hot chicken. the hot chicken sandwich with the ""hot"" level is absolutely perfect. the taste, the spice, the slaw. it's perfect. the fries are so good and the ranch is yummy. the pimento mac n cheese is so creamy and to die for. the beans are very good as well. i get the same thing every time and i want to go every week lol i haven't been since covid, but before there was always a line. no matter what time of day or what day of the week. the line never bothered me because it's so good. there's not a ton of space inside, but i've always had a table to matter how packed it is. the staff is always friendly and we get the food in a decent amount of time. love love love this place."
"Hattie B's Moreland Ave location gets 4.5 stars rounded up to 5 from me. I thought the food here was excellent and better than my last experience at Hattie B's Melrose location in Nashville, which was already good to begin with: bit.ly/34NzGyH.Since opening their first location in Atlanta in July 2018, Hattie B's has been a local hot spot with lines out the door. This place is popular. I don't like waiting in line for food, especially at hyped-up new restaurants; it's just not worth it to me, so I deliberately waited well over a year before trying this location. We showed up around 12:50pm on a Saturday. We got a free parking spot next to the restaurant and there were only three groups ahead of us in line. The dining room, however, was already packed and around 1:00pm, a small line had built up that spilled out of the entrance. We got lucky.Free parking is limited. According to a sign posted at the counter, there are only 19 free spots around the building. In addition to those free spots, you can park for free at the Sherwin-Williams next door after hours. If you can't find any free spots then you'll have to park at the adjacent surface lot, owned by Front Page News, and pay. Outside, there's clear signage describing the parking situation.This is a fast-casual restaurant. Order dine-in or takeout at the counter. If dining in, your order will be brought to your table. Staff is responsible for bussing tables. Soda, tea, and water are self-serve. They have taps (local draft) in additional to cans and bottles of craft and domestic beer. The dining room has large TVs. Outside, the patio is covered and has both fans and heating. It was busy, but we had no problems finding seating.The chain's menu is the same here as in Nashville. Hattie B's fried chicken comes in six spice levels, from ""Southern"" (no heat) to ""Shut the Cluck Up!!!"" (hottest). My friends and I tried Shut the Cluck Up!!! in Nashville and it was too spicy for me to enjoy the food. I love spicy food and ""Hot!"" (two levels below Shut the Cluck Up!!!) is what I like. If you can't handle spicy food, I wouldn't go higher than ""Medium."" Note there is a big jump in spice from Medium to Hot!In addition to chicken plates (breasts, wings, legs, thighs), you can get tenders, whole wings, and chicken sandwiches. There are a variety of Southern sides and desserts. Chicken and waffles and special bacon cheese grits are available on Sundays only.Here's what we got:* Large Dark Plate ($10.50) - two leg and thigh quarters, two sides (Southern greens, pimento mac & cheese), bread, and pickles* Wings ($10) - three whole wings, two sides (creamy coleslaw, black eyed pea salad), and pickle* Chicken Sandwich ($9) - chicken breast, coleslaw, Nashville ""Comeback"" sauce, kosher pickle, side (Southern greens)* Banana Pudding ($3)* Peach Cobbler ($3)Everything was great -- chicken, sides, and dessert. Oftentimes, a fried chicken or BBQ restaurant might excel in one or two areas (good meats, but lackluster sides or vice versa), but this Hattie B's hit on all cylinders. The food not only looked great, but it tasted great too. Our entire order was brought out together.I can't say I preferred the one chicken plate/sandwich over another. They were all equally delectable. The portion sizes were generous. All of the chicken was cooked to perfection. Delectably crispy and well-seasoned skin on the outside with juicy and tender meat on the inside. Incredibly gratifying. Every bite was pleasurable. I really like how Hattie B's is able to put out such delicious fried chicken that's not too greasy (like Popeye's). Their chicken is subtly sweet, the milder flavors more so than the hot. Hot! flavors and above come with an extra spicy dry rub so be careful not to inhale it. The heat is real.The chicken can get messy to eat, especially the sandwich, which overflows with coleslaw. It'd be nice if they provided wet naps. If eating Hot! chicken or above, don't accidentally rub your eyes.All of the sides were terrific. I love collard greens so I'd have to say I personally liked the greens the best, especially after adding pepper-vinegar sauce, supplied in a condiment bucket at the table. The greens were wonderfully-flavored and savory. The pimento mac & cheese was fantastic. Rich, smooth, and creamy. The slaw was solid as well. I recommend the slaw if you order Hot! chicken or above. Because of the creamy mayo, it's the most ideal side for dousing the flames in your mouth. This visit was my first trying the black eyed pea salad and I was pleasantly surprised. It was cold, fresh, and refreshing. Definitely worth trying.If there was anything weak to our meal, it was the peach cobbler. It needed to be sweeter and have more crusty texture. It was a little too goopy. The banana pudding was outstanding and way better. I'd put Hattie B's banana pudding up against the best banana puddings in Atlanta because it would have a great chance at winning."
This chicken is everything !! Amazingly crisp with the just the eight level of spice  and Juicy !! The sides are phenomenal !! The consistent line at this place is proof that the food is delicious!! My secret !! I use Yelp Delivery options !! Food arrives rather quickly and no line !!! WIN WIN
"Hattie B's has perfected spicy chicken. This was hard for me to admit, as I am from New Orleans and have strong feelings about Louisiana chicken, but nothing that I've had beats Hattie b's. It's even worth the really long wait. I usually get the grilled chicken sandwich. I've also had fried, which is still mind-blowing, but for some reason I like the grilled better--I think I can just taste the chicken and it's flavor better this way. Speaking of flavor, I usually alternate between hot and damn hot when it comes to spice level. I've never gotten the hottest option and I can't imagine doing so unless I had something to prove, as damn hot already has me taking breaks between bites.I also love the flavoring of the fries which I think tastes so great when dipped in the honey mustard sauce or just soaked in the sauce that the chicken is cooked in.Regardless of your spice level, your preferences for grilled or fried, or even what part of the bird you're looking for, Hattie Bs has an excellent option for you. The variety and quality of the sides is also impressive.Im so thankful for this Atlanta location!"
