"This spot was open with outside patio seating requiring social distancing and masks which was great because COVID-19 is still around. They had quick and easy parking today (Saturday) during lunch even though they had a line to the street which was unbelievable. My fiancé was able to find us a table and we waited about 10-12 minutes before we got our food. FAST! They also have contactless payments options and a great system for ordering and picking up your food. I ordered the Jumbo Chicken Fingers (3) [Southern Style- no heat] with Pimento Mac and seasoned French fries with an extra wing on the side ($1) My fiancé ordered the 3 Wing Meal (Mild - which is a hint of heat) with Baked Beans & Pimento Mac. In addition, we ordered there famous Peach Cobbler, there famous sauce, ranch & honey mustard dressings & 2 lemonades to drink. They gave us utensils and napkins in the bag which was great! All meals came with bread and a pickle. If you're going to go just get the fried chicken. The wings were BOMB! Extremely juicy on the inside yet crunch and battered perfectly on the outside. The Mild wings didn't have any kick to it but the flavor was definitely there. I didn't care for the chicken tenders being they were a little dry on the inside and tasted like they had been in the holding well for too long. The pimento Mac was alright. I needed to add a little salt, but it's nothing I would order again. I enjoyed the baked beans but again...nothing to ride home about. The fries were AMAZING and the seasoning was incredible. Now this peach cobbler y'all MAAAAAAANNNNN hands down the best I've ever had! The crust was to die for and the peach center had just enough sweetness to off balance the crust. I would've eaten 5 of these if I could. The Lemonades were very refreshing especially on a sunny Fall day and after eating some great fried chicken. There customer service was outstanding and I would definitely be back again! I spent about $35 for everything today! Would I come back? Hell yeah!!!!"
