"Hattie B's has been on my radar for a hot second, but every time I pass the place, there's a mile-long line shooting out of it. Well, I decided what better time to give Hattie's a visit than now, with everything that's going on in the world - there surely couldn't be a group of folks waiting outside. I went on a Saturday, after calling in a takeout order, and rightfully so, there were only a few ppl waiting outside of the doors for their food. Hattie B's menu is pretty clear cut, they have chicken plates available, with quarter options, your typical southern side dishes (mac, baked beans, potato salad, greens, cole slaw, French fries, black eyed pea salad), some desserts, and their very famous hot chicken sandwich. I opted for the chicken sandwich with a side of their pimiento Mac and cheese and banana pudding. They have heat levels for the chicken ranging from Southern (no heat) to Shut the Cluck Up (burn notice, yikes). I went with the medium level and let me tell you, that is probably the hottest I'll go. The heat at this level isn't painful, but it leaves you with a lingering heat. I did find myself sniffling a bit and it did make eating the sandwich a little less enjoyable. Now I know though! I will say that the chicken was a bit dry, not moist and juicy like I prefer. The bottom bun was also soaked in grease which made for a limp and soggy base for my sandwich. I did like the pickle and the slaw on the sandwich. It cuts through the spice and provides a nice refreshing crunch to your bite. I just wish I had gotten a juicier piece of chicken.The mac and cheese was okay, nothing to run home about. It was creamy and had a little kick to it as well. The banana pudding was also just okay. Most of the banana slices in it were a bit tough and did not taste ripe. I can't speak to the inside of the restaurant as they were not allowing people to go inside (right now they are just filling to-go orders). The parking situation is very tight and limited, so be aware of that. I would return to Hattie's and give them another shot. I've heard too many good things about the chicken sandwich and will hopefully get a nice juicy piece of chicken next time! (most likely at the mild heat level)"
